A man was hit by a train and killed as he attempted to flee from police.

The suspect, believed to be in his 20s, was stopped by officers just before 4pm in Christchurch Avenue, Willesden Green, north west London, as they believed him to have drugs.

After a short period, the man made off on foot with the officers in pursuit.

