Following a chase which lasted around 40 minutes and involved the suspect running through gardens, climbing over fences and across railway lines, he was hit by a train on the line near Dartmouth Road, Willesden, at 5.12pm.

London Ambulance Service attended but the man was pronounced dead at the scene, a Metropolitan Police spokesman said.

